    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM DRIVE AXLES: EATON - IDENTIFICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>IDENTIFICATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Text and illustrations provided by Eaton Corporation.</para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
            <title>AXLE AND CARRIER</title>
            <para>Eaton identifies a tandem axle by the nomenclature assigned to the forward axle. Differential carrier
                identification is stamped on a metal tag attached to the carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401301">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401301" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401301" filename="../figg14/G1401301.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Carrier Identification</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>MODEL-Axle model identification</para>
            <para>HEAD-Carrier assembly part number</para>
            <para>RATIO-Axle ratio</para>
            <para>SPEC-This number identifies all Eaton built component parts, and special OEM requirements</para>
            <para>SERIAL NO.-Carrier assembly serial number and date code</para>
            <para>CUST. PART NO.-OEM part number which equates to Eaton specification number</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
